&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Accounting Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Dalio Family Office Overview: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dalio Family Office (DFO) supports Barbara and Ray Dalio and their family in their ventures, investments, and philanthropic efforts under Dalio Philanthropies, which includes OceanX, Dalio Education, Endless Network, and the Beijing Dalio Foundation. The core of the DFO’s culture is built around meaningful work and meaningful relationships and the family’s commitment to giving back. The office is headquartered in Westport, CT with regional offices in New York City, Singapore, and Abu Dhabi.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Accounting Associate, you’ll take ownership of core bookkeeping and accounting activities across our entities while leading key projects and processes within the accounting function. This role offers meaningful exposure to a wide range of accounting and investment‑related work, with the opportunity to tackle new challenges every day, contribute to process improvement, and build long‑term, trusted partnerships across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Day-to-day responsibilities would include a combination of the following:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and perform complex bookkeeping and accounting activities for investment and operating entities, including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executing day-to-day general ledger activity as part of the monthly close process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining general ledgers used for tax and financial reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing bank, credit card, and balance sheet reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing cash management activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing and maintaining schedules, analyses, and reports to support tax return preparation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and analyze information across investment reports, including capital gains, interest and dividend income, and alternative and fixed income securities, and appropriately book related activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive key accounting and financial projects and recurring processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review disbursements, reconciliations, credit card transactions, general ledger activity, and financial statements to ensure accuracy and completeness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify areas of risk or inefficiency and design and implement solutions or process improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal stakeholders and provide accounting support as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties and special projects as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The ideal candidate will possess the following knowledge, skills, attributes, and values:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driven to achieve excellence – high standards and expectations   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and reliable   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to synthesize, report, and analyze information   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage and drive multiple initiatives to completion   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to work independently with excellent judgment and discretion   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills   &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in a fast-paced, fluid environment and be comfortable navigating ambiguity &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Illustrative Benefits: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% company paid medical premiums&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;17 company paid holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friday summer hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly community happy hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free catered food services for in-office days&lt;/li&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior FinTech Recruiting Associate&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dalio Family Office&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Dalio Family Office Overview: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dalio Family Office (DFO) supports Barbara and Ray Dalio and their family in their ventures, investments, and philanthropic efforts under Dalio Philanthropies, which includes OceanX, Dalio Education, Endless Network, and the Beijing Dalio Foundation. The core of the DFO’s culture is built around meaningful work and meaningful relationships and the family’s commitment to giving back. The office is headquartered in Westport, CT with regional offices in New York City, Singapore, and Abu Dhabi.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DFO is seeking an experienced and savvy Senior (FinTech) Recruiting Associate to manage and operate our FinTech search portfolio. This role will require flexibility to work international hours based out of our U.S. offices and support the entirety of our FinTech based needs. We are looking for an experienced Senior Recruiting Associate who thinks in terms of pipelines not requisitions, building a pipeline of talent through our various networks, and prepared to address our growing business needs thoughtfully – holding compliance and governance in the highest regard. The Senior Recruiting Associate should have a crisp understanding of what engineers and tech professionals are looking for, and can effectively speak their language to identify the best talent globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Day-to-day responsibilities would include a combination of the following:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-cycle ownership — manage requisitions from intake through offer acceptance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hiring manager partnership — conduct structured intake sessions, set search strategy, calibrate on candidate profiles, and provides market intelligence to align expectations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing strategy — build proactive pipelines through direct outreach and Boolean search&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agency management – collaborate effectively, autonomously, and&amp;nbsp;thoughtfully with agency partnerships, bearing in mind key strategies and industry standards.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate experience — deliver consistent, high-quality experience at every touchpoint; represent the company with professionalism and transparency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data &amp;amp; reporting — track and own recruiting metrics (time-to-fill, source-of-hire, offer acceptance rate, pipeline conversion) and use data to improve&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; process integrity — ensure all hiring activities adhere to employment law, EEO requirements, and internal audit standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer management — construct competitive, legally sound offers; negotiate with candidates using market data and internal compensation frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional duties as assigned&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
